rom those held by social theorists. Surprising and provocative, Citizens, Cops, and Power provides a critical perspective not only on the future of community policing, but on the nature of state-society relations as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  acommunity, law enforcement, policing, crime, urban, city, trust, race, neighborhood, beat cop, nonfiction, collaboration, police, citizen participation, prevention, legitimacy, legal system, criminal justice, arrests, racism, governance, government, politics, democracy, social change, criminology, sociology, stop and frisk, search.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022632730340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226327358423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226327358/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles